FBIS4-19971 "drweu079_i_94005" FBIS-WEU-94-079 Daily Report 23 Apr 1994 FRANCE Politicians React to Nixon's Death Politicians React to Nixon's Death LD2304140394 Paris France-2 Teletext in French 1342 GMT 23 Apr 94 LD2304140394 Paris France-2 Teletext French BFN [Text] In a message of condolences sent to his eldest daughter, President Francois Mitterrand has mentioned the "great role" played by Nixon "on the international scene." Former President Valery Giscard D'Estaing commemorated Nixon by stressing the fact that "under his presidency relations between France and the United States were excellent." Jacques Chirac, mayor of Paris and former prime minister, said that "Nixon was the man who put an end to the war in Vietnam and who started a dialogue with the communist world."
